 {"id":"bd-3h3","title":"Create fastmcp-console crate skeleton","description":"# Create fastmcp-console Crate Skeleton

## Purpose
This is the FOUNDATIONAL task for the entire rich_rust integration. Every other task in this epic depends on this crate existing. The fastmcp-console crate will house all rich terminal output functionality, keeping it cleanly separated from protocol concerns.

## Why a Separate Crate?
1. **Separation of Concerns**: Console output is orthogonal to MCP protocol
2. **Optional Dependency**: Projects can use FastMCP without rich output
3. **Testing Isolation**: Rich output can be tested independently
4. **Feature Flags**: Can gate rich_rust dependency behind feature flags
5. **Build Time**: Optional compilation of rich features

